    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9200, 9300 &#38; 9400 MODELS - TROUBLESHOOTING
        - TESTING TRACTION CONTROL MODULATOR, PART B
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING TRACTION CONTROL MODULATOR, PART B</title>
        <table id="t0403422" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Traction Control Modulator, Part B</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.24in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.99in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (350), measure resistance at terminals D2 and D3 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect (360) from the traction control solenoid. At controller side of connector
                                measure resistance to ground at both terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Locate short to ground in chassis harness circuits 94BB and 94BA, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace the traction control solenoid/pigtail assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (350) measure resistance between circuit 94BB and 94BA and all other
                                circuits in connector (350).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Make sure connectors (350) and (360) are clean, free of damage and reconnect. Turn Key
                                ON and use magnet to reset LEDs. Repeat
                                <hotlnk document="s04034_7.xml" xrefid="t0403401">INITIAL START-UP TEST PROCEDURE
                                    <xref refid="t0403401"/>
                                </hotlnk>
                                .
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate short between any circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                ohms, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
